Certainly! The `bind()` function in the context of a server socket is used to associate the socket with a specific IP address and port number. This allows the server to listen for incoming connections on that address and port.

Here's how you would typically use `bind()` in the context of your `WebServer::start()` function:

1. **Create the socket**: This is already done with the [`socket()`](command:_github.copilot.openSymbolFromReferences?%5B%22%22%2C%5B%7B%22uri%22%3A%7B%22scheme%22%3A%22file%22%2C%22authority%22%3A%22%22%2C%22path%22%3A%22%2Fhome%2Flotse%2Fcode%2Fneaarxh%2Fcodam%2FRank_5%2Fwebserv%2FWebServer.cpp%22%2C%22query%22%3A%22%22%2C%22fragment%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%22pos%22%3A%7B%22line%22%3A45%2C%22character%22%3A13%7D%7D%5D%2C%22849389a0-c209-4acc-8afd-f52d21ee9dc7%22%5D "Go to definition") function.
