3. **Prepare the address structure**: This is partially done in your code.
4. **Bind the socket**: This is the step where you use `bind()` to associate the socket with the address and port.

Let's add the `bind()` function to your `WebServer::start()` method:

### Pseudocode
1. Create the socket.
2. Set socket options.
3. Prepare the address structure.
4. Bind the socket to the address and port.
5. Handle any errors that occur during binding.

### Updated Code
```cpp
void WebServer::start()
{
    struct sockaddr_in address;
    int sock_opt;
    int opt = 1;                

    // Create server fd
    server_fd = socket(AF_INET, SOCK_STREAM, 0);
    if (server_fd == -1)
    {
        // std::cerr << "Failed to create server socket" << std::endl;
        handleError(strerror(errno));
    }

    // Adjust socket options
    sock_opt = setsockopt(server_fd, SOL_SOCKET, SO_REUSEADDR | SO_REUSEPORT, &opt, sizeof(opt));
    if (sock_opt == -1)
    {
        // std::cerr << "Failed to set socket options << std::endl;
        handleError(strerror(errno));
    }

    address.sin_family = AF_INET;
    address.sin_addr.s_addr = INADDR_ANY;
    address.sin_port = htons(port);

    // Bind the socket to the address and port
    if (bind(server_fd, (struct sockaddr *)&address, sizeof(address)) < 0)
    {
        // std::cerr << "Failed to bind to port" << std::endl;
        handleError(strerror(errno));
    }
}
```

### Explanation
- **`bind(server_fd, (struct sockaddr *)&address, sizeof(address))`**: This function call binds the socket [`server_fd`](command:_github.copilot.openSymbolFromReferences?%5B%22%22%2C%5B%7B%22uri%22%3A%7B%22scheme%22%3A%22file%22%2C%22authority%22%3A%22%22%2C%22path%22%3A%22%2Fhome%2Flotse%2Fcode%2Fneaarxh%2Fcodam%2FRank_5%2Fwebserv%2FWebServer.cpp%22%2C%22query%22%3A%22%22%2C%22fragment%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%22pos%22%3A%7B%22line%22%3A45%2C%22character%22%3A1%7D%7D%5D%2C%22849389a0-c209-4acc-8afd-f52d21ee9dc7%22%5D "Go to definition") to the address and port specified in the [`address`](command:_github.copilot.openSymbolFromReferences?%5B%22%22%2C%5B%7B%22uri%22%3A%7B%22scheme%22%3A%22file%22%2C%22authority%22%3A%22%22%2C%22path%22%3A%22%2Fhome%2Flotse%2Fcode%2Fneaarxh%2Fcodam%2FRank_5%2Fwebserv%2FWebServer.cpp%22%2C%22query%22%3A%22%22%2C%22fragment%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%22pos%22%3A%7B%22line%22%3A40%2C%22character%22%3A20%7D%7D%5D%2C%22849389a0-c209-4acc-8afd-f52d21ee9dc7%22%5D "Go to definition") structure.
